# TEC.ERP AI Coach Architecture

Read `docs/09_AI_COACH_ARCHITECTURE.md` before implementing any AI or coach feature.

## Role

The AI Coach is a **pedagogical assistant** that supports student reasoning and professor guidance. It must **not** replace student decision-making or the professor.

## Core Principles (AI-001–006)

| ID | Rule |
|----|------|
| AI-001 | Coach, not answer engine — ask questions, explain consequences |
| AI-002 | Context-aware — feedback tied to mission, decision, KPI impact |
| AI-003 | Professional business language adapted to student level |
| AI-004 | Progressive guidance: simple (M1–M2) → process impact (M3–M8) → challenge reasoning (M9–M10) |
| AI-005 | Traceable — store feedback linked to mission attempt |
| AI-006 | Professor visibility — review patterns at student and cohort level |

## Allowed Functions

Mission feedback · Reflection prompts · Error explanation · Recommendation support (M9–M10) · Professor insights (`docs/09` §AI Coach Functions).

## Prohibited Behavior

- Giving direct answers that bypass student analysis
- Making business decisions on behalf of the student
- Operating without mission and KPI context
- Storing or exposing data without security controls (`docs/26`)

## Implementation Notes

- AI provider configuration via environment variables — never hardcoded (`docs/19` §78)
- Feedback generation must be auditable and linked to learning history
- Align with Simulation Engine outcomes for consequence explanations (`docs/06`, `docs/09`)
